cast.overview: A woman married to a former politician during the 1971 military dictatorship in Brazil is forced to reinvent herself and chart a new course for her family after a violent and arbitrary act.
cast.title: I'm Still Here

details.biography: Maeve Jinkings Melo Silva (Brasília, August 4, 1976) is a Brazilian actress. Known primarily for starring in small-scale independent films with dramatic themes, she has received several awards, including two Guarani Awards, and two Best Actress awards at the Brasília Festival, as well as receiving nominations for two Grande Otelo awards.
details.name: Maeve Jinkings
